This is a script to meant to automate node_exporter installation from source and create a daemon to make sure is always running, in a nutshell this are the steps taken:

## Installing and Configuring Node_Exporter from Source

1. Download the latest version of node_exporter source code from the official GitHub repository:

   ```
   git clone https://github.com/prometheus/node_exporter.git
   ```

2. Change to the extracted directory:

   ```
   cd node_exporter-1.2.2
   ```

3. Build node_exporter using the make command:

   ```
   make
   ```

4. Create a system user to run node_exporter:

   ```
   sudo useradd --no-create-home --shell /bin/false node_exporter
   ```

5. Copy the node_exporter binary to /usr/local/bin:

   ```
   sudo cp node_exporter /usr/local/bin
   ```

6. Set the ownership of the binary to the node_exporter user:

   ```
   sudo chown node_exporter:node_exporter /usr/local/bin/node_exporter
   ```

7. Create a systemd service file for node_exporter:

   ```
   sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/node_exporter.service
   ```

8. Paste the following contents into the file:

   ```
   [Unit]
   Description=Node Exporter
   After=network.target

   [Service]
   User=node_exporter
   Group=node_exporter
   Type=simple
   ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/node_exporter

   [Install]
   WantedBy=multi-user.target
   ```

9. Save and close the file by pressing `Ctrl+X`, `Y`, and `Enter`.

10. Reload the systemd daemon to read the new service file:

    ```
    sudo systemctl daemon-reload
    ```

11. Start the node_exporter service:

    ```
    sudo systemctl start node_exporter
    ```

12. Verify that the service is running:

    ```
    sudo systemctl status node_exporter
    ```

13. Enable the service to start at boot:

    ```
    sudo systemctl enable node_exporter
    ```

That's it! You have now installed and configured node_exporter from source.
